# Recall Touch — Operational Guidelines

When building features for Recall Touch:

## Show outcomes
- Calls answered, leads captured, appointments booked, revenue impact
- Stat cards with animated numbers, trend arrows, sparklines
- Charts and visualizations for analytics (area, donut, heatmap, funnel)

## Show what needs attention
- Missed calls, hot leads not yet contacted, stalled follow-ups
- Upcoming appointments, failed integrations, usage limits approaching

## Show activity
- Real-time feed of calls, leads, appointments, SMS, and system events
- Timeline components with timestamps, outcomes, and quick actions

## Enable action
- Quick paths to: make a call, send SMS, add lead, create agent, run campaign
- Command palette (⌘K) for global search and actions
- Inline actions on list items (play audio, view transcript, add to leads)

## UI feel
- Premium dark theme — Linear/Vercel quality
- Smooth Framer Motion animations on all transitions
- Skeleton loading states matching actual layout
- Cards with subtle borders and hover effects
- Proper focus-visible rings for accessibility

## Engineering
- Server Components by default
- Supabase Realtime for live updates where applicable
- Optimistic UI for CRUD operations
- Proper error boundaries on every route
- All user-visible data from stored events in Supabase
